==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eliquation
<hw>El`i*qua"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>eliquatio</ets>, fr. <ets>eliquare</ets> to clarify, strain;
<ets>e</ets> + <ets>liquare</ets> to make liquid, melt.]</ety>
<fld>(Metallurgy)</fld> <def>The process of separating a fusible
substance from one less fusible, by means of a degree of heat sufficient
to melt the one and not the other, as an alloy of copper and lead;
liquation.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elison</ent>⟦br⟧
